§212 If it first belong to the heir after the death of the testator it is a question whether the bequest is valid, and it is generally held to be invalid. However, even though a thing bequeathed never belonged either to the testator or to the heir, by the senatusconsult of Nero all bequests are put on the same foot- ing as a bequest by condemnation.
